W000560.bio:
a Representative from Georgia; 
born in Frederick County, Va., January 5, 1745; 
received a liberal education; 
served as captain and colonel in the Revolutionary War in 1777 and 1778; 
moved to Wilkes County, Ga., in 1784; 
elected to the Second Congress (March 4, 1791-March 3, 1793); 
moved to Maury County, Tenn.; 
died January 25, 1829.
